•   The Truth and Reconciliation Commission,  currently investigating the Norwegian treatment  of and the injustices done against the Sami population, which is set to deliver a report to the  Presidium of the Parliament on September 1, 2022;  

 •   The Scandinavian Star Commission,  which investigated the fire on an M/S Scandinavian  Star cruise ship in 1990 where 159 passengers and crew members died (including 136  Norwegians) and presented its report on June 1, 2017;  

 •   The Mehamn Commission 15  (2003–2005), which investigated the Twin Otter LN-BKN  accident near Gamvik on March 11, 1982; and 

 •   The Lund Commission 16  (1994–1996) which investigated  accusations of unlawful surveillance  of groups of Norwegian citizens by the Norwegian security police and branches of the armed  forces following 1945.
